Program: Outlook
Title: 16/01/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00mv17x
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 17 Jan 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Londoner Duwayne Brooks remembers the night his school friend Stephen Lawrence was fatally stabbed in front of him by a racist gang. Duwayne was the only witness, and he tells Matthew Bannister how his life has been changed over the 18 years it has taken to bring Stephen's killers to justice. (Image: Duwayne Brooks. Credit: Lewisham Council) Show less